The solution of differential equation<br>\[
x \frac{d y}{d x}+2 y=x^{2} \text { is }
\]

questions.solution:
Given differential equations,<br>\[
\begin{array}{l}
x \frac{d y}{d x}+2 y=x^{2} \\
\Rightarrow \frac{d y}{d x}+\frac{2 y}{x}=x \rightarrow(1)
\end{array}
\]<br>General differential equation of this type is given by<br>\[
\frac{d y}{d x}+P(x) y=Q(x)
\]<br>So, \( P=\frac{2}{x} \) then I.F. factor is given by<br>\[
e^{\int P d x}=e^{\int \frac{2}{x} d x}=e^{2 \log x}=e^{\log x^{2}}=x^{2}
\]<br>Then, \( x^{2} \frac{d y}{d x}+2 x y=x^{3} \)<br>\[
\Rightarrow \frac{d}{d x}\left(x^{2} y\right)=x^{3}
\]<br>Integrating both the sides, we get<br>\[
\begin{array}{l}
x^{2} y=\frac{x^{4}}{4}+C_{1} \\
\Rightarrow x^{2} y=\frac{x^{4}+C}{4} \\
\Rightarrow y=\frac{x^{4}+C}{4 x^{2}}
\end{array}
\]

